            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-12-05T11:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-12-05T11:30:00-05:00" n="475" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Marquis of Salisbury</gloss>
                                to Consul <persName type="to">Cusack-Smith</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegraphic, P.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign
                                        Office</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-12-05T16:30:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 5,
                                        1891–430p.m</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">[Navigator Islands, December 5; confidential, 81; section
                            1.]</p>
                <p rend="center">No. 1.</p>
                <p>Yon should unite with the German consul in urging the Samoan Government
                            to take measures in accordance with the request of the municipal council
                            of the 3d June and of the 24th July last respecting the currency
                            question.</p>
                <p>Her Majesty’s minister at Washington will be instructed to urge the U. S.
                            Government to issue similar directions to the American consul.</p>
            </div>
